{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/spacer\/fixedsize()"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Spacer\/fixedSize()"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Spacer"]]},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fixedSize","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"ideal size","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" of its children both dimensions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"may not be the effect you want.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can think of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" as the creation of a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"counter proposal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view, and the specific effects of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" depends on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"particular view and how you have configured it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertical dimensions, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)","type"